results.name: Product of "digit values" in Semigreedy Catalan Representation of n, A244159.
comment: Note that a(33604) = 10! = 3628800 because the product is computed from the underlying list (vector) of numbers, and thus is not subject to any corruption by decimal representation as A244159 itself is.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..4862
program: (Scheme) (define (A244233 n) (apply * (vector->list (A244159raw n)))) ;; A244159raw given in A244159.
xref: A244314 gives the positions of zeros.
